  2→/**
  3→ * @file Main HTTP server for the MCP server
  4→ * @module server
  5→ * 
  6→ * @remarks
  7→ * This module provides the Express.js HTTP server that handles:
  8→ * - OAuth 2.1 authentication flows (Steps 1-8 of MCP OAuth spec)
  9→ * - MCP protocol endpoints with authentication
 10→ * - Health checks and metadata endpoints
 11→ * 
 12→ * OAuth Flow Integration:
 13→ * @see https://modelcontextprotocol.io/specification/2025-06-18/basic/authorization
 14→ * 
 15→ * 1. Client requests /mcp without auth → 401 with WWW-Authenticate
 16→ * 2. Client discovers metadata endpoints from WWW-Authenticate
 17→ * 3. Client gets auth server info from /.well-known endpoints
 18→ * 4. Client optionally registers at /oauth/register
 19→ * 5. User authorizes at /oauth/authorize
 20→ * 6. Authorization server redirects back with an authorization code
 21→ * 7. Client exchanges code at /oauth/token
 22→ * 8. Client uses JWT token for authenticated /mcp requests
 23→ * 
 24→ * The server can be run standalone or integrated with platforms like Smithery.
 25→ */
